## 9. ASSEMBLY PROCEDURES\par
\par
### 9.1 Phase 1: Magnetic Array Assembly\par
\par
**Step 1: Plate Preparation**\par
```\par
1. Clean PTFE plate with isopropyl alcohol (99%)\par
2. Inspect all holes for burrs (PTFE is soft)\par
3. Verify hole positions with coordinate measuring machine\par
4. Apply masking to areas not receiving adhesive\par
```\par
\par
**Step 2: Magnet Installation**\par
```\par
1. Verify polarity of all magnets (mark North pole)\par
2. Apply PTFE primer to magnet pockets (if using epoxy)\par
3. Mix epoxy: Loctite 392 or Stycast 2850FT\par
4. Apply 0.002" epoxy layer to pocket bottom\par
5. Insert magnet with North pole UP (verify with compass)\par
6. Press firmly to seat (5-10 lbs force)\par
7. Wipe excess epoxy with alcohol\par
8. Cure: 24 hours at 72\'b0F (22\'b0C)\par
9. Verify final polarity of all magnets\par
```\par
\par
**Step 3: Field Verification**\par
```\par
1. Measure surface field at center of each magnet\par
2. Record values: Expected 5,500 \'b1500 Gauss\par
3. Map field 0.250" above array\par
4. Verify hexagonal symmetry\par
5. Document for baseline\par
```\par
\par
### 9.2 Phase 2: Coil Winding\par
\par
**Step 1: Mandrel Setup**\par
```\par
1. Mount mandrel in lathe or winding machine\par
2. Install tensioner set to 100g\par
3. Prepare two spools of wire (matched lengths)\par
4. Clean mandrel surface with alcohol\par
```\par
\par
**Step 2: Bifilar Winding**\par
```\par
1. Start both wires together at flange\par
2. Maintain 0.022" side-by-side spacing\par
3. Wind 22 turns (baseline) or 18 turns (optimized)\par
4. Maintain tension constant throughout\par
5. Apply thin CA glue every 5 turns to secure\par
6. At end, secure with tape\par
7. Measure inductance: Should be 68 \'b5H \'b15% (baseline)\par
```\par
\par
**Step 3: Termination**\par
```\par
1. Strip ends: 0.25" (6.35 mm)\par
2. Tin with solder (63/37, 350\'b0C)\par
3. Connect start of strand 1 to end of strand 2\par
4. Label remaining ends: Coil+ and Coil-\par
5. Apply heat shrink over connections\par
6. Measure final DC resistance\par
```\par
\par
### 9.3 Phase 3: Electronics Assembly\par
\par
**Step 1: PCB Population**\par
```\par
1. Solder all surface-mount components first\par
2. Use hot air reflow at 260\'b0C (leaded) or 280\'b0C (lead-free)\par
3. Inspect under microscope\par
4. Solder through-hole components\par
5. Clean flux with alcohol\par
```\par
\par
**Step 2: Power Stage Testing**\par
```\par
1. Apply low voltage (12V) with no load\par
2. Verify gate drive waveforms (10V p-p)\par
3. Check for oscillations\par
4. Increase to 48V with dummy load (10\f2\lang1032\'d9 resistor)\par
5. Verify current limiting\par
```\par
\par
**Step 3: Control Loop Integration**\par
```\par
1. Load firmware/FPGA configuration\par
2. Verify frequency output: 148.5 kHz \f0\lang1033\'b1100 Hz\par
3. Test manual frequency sweep: \'b15 kHz\par
4. Enable auto-resonance tracking\par
