## 10. CALIBRATION & VERIFICATION PROTOCOLS\par
\par
### 10.1 Initial Power-Up Sequence\par
\par
```\par
Step 1: Low Power Check\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Set PWM: 148.5 kHz, 10% duty cycle\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Apply 48V DC\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Monitor current: Should be < 1A\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Verify no overheating after 2 minutes\par
\f7\u9492?\u9472?\f0  Log all readings\par
\par
Step 2: Resonance Search\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Increase duty cycle to 50%\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Sweep frequency: 145-152 kHz in 100 Hz steps\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Record current at each frequency\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Identify frequency of minimum current (resonance)\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Difference from 148.5 kHz indicates capacitance tolerance\par
\f7\u9492?\u9472?\f0  Adjust capacitor trim if needed\par
\par
Step 3: Power Ramp\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Increase voltage in 10V steps to 120V\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Monitor current at resonance\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Verify linear relationship (I \f5\u8733?\f0  V)\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Check for thermal runaway\par
\f7\u9492?\u9472?\f0  Maximum current at 120V: 5.0A \'b10.2A\par
```\par
\par
### 10.2 Null Detection Calibration\par
\par
**Equipment Required:**\par
```\par
- Precision translation stage (0.001" resolution)\par
- Hall probe with axial tip (0.020" diameter)\par
- Gauss meter with >200 kHz bandwidth\par
- Digital storage oscilloscope\par
- Spectrum analyzer\par
```\par
\par
**Procedure:**\par
```\par
1. Position Hall probe 0.250" above center magnet\par
2. Set frequency to resonance (from Section 10.1)\par
3. Set voltage to 48V\par
4. Record B-field vs. current (0-5A in 0.1A steps)\par
5. Identify current where B-field is minimum\par
6. Move probe in X and Y directions (0.020" steps)\par
7. Map null region in 3D\par
8. Document null diameter (FWHM)\par
9. Repeat at different heights (0.125" to 0.750")\par
10. Identify optimal coil height\par
```\par
\par
**Acceptance Criteria:**\par
```\par
Baseline: Null < 50 Gauss over 0.125" sphere\par
Optimized: Null < 10 Gauss over 0.125" sphere\par
Ultimate: Null < 1 pT over 0.010" sphere (requires atomic magnetometer)\par
```\par
\par
### 10.3 Active-Silence Verification\par
\par
**Procedure:**\par
```\par
1. Set coil height to optimal position (from 10.2)\par
2. Set frequency to resonance\par
3. Set current to null current (from 10.2)\par
4. Record:\par
   \f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  B-field at center (should be minimum)\par
   \f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  A-field via pickup coil (should be maximum)\par
   \f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Phase between voltage and current (should be 0\'b0)\par
   \f7\u9492?\u9472?\f0  Harmonic content (should be minimum)\par
5. Hold condition for 1 hour\par
6. Monitor stability of null\par
7. Record temperature every minute\par
8. Repeat at 3 different power levels (80V, 100V, 120V)\par
9. Repeat at 5 different center positions (within 0.050")\par
10. Statistical analysis of null quality\par
```\par
\par
### 10.4 Frequency Stability Test\par
\par
**Procedure:**\par
```\par
1. Set system to Active-Silence condition\par
2. Record frequency every second for 24 hours\par
3. Calculate Allan deviation\par
4. Measure phase noise with spectrum analyzer\par
5. Measure temperature at 10 points\par
6. Correlate frequency drift with temperature\par
```\par
\par
**Acceptance Criteria:**\par
```\par
Baseline: \'b110 Hz over 24 hours\par
Optimized: \'b10.5 Hz over 24 hours\par
Ultimate: \'b10.0001 Hz over 24 hours (atomic clock referenced)\par
```\par
\par
### 10.5 Thermal Performance Test\par
\par
**Procedure:**\par
```\par
1. Install thermocouples at:\par
   \f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Coil center\par
   \f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  PTFE plate (under center magnet)\par
   \f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  TEC hot side (if used)\par
   \f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  TEC cold side (if used)\par
   \f7\u9492?\u9472?\f0  Ambient air\par
2. Run at 240W for 2 hours\par
3. Log temperatures every 10 seconds\par
4. Calculate thermal resistance\par
5. Verify all temperatures < 60\'b0C (baseline) or < 45\'b0C (optimized)\par
```\par
