## 11. SAFETY SYSTEMS & INTERLOCKS\par
\par
### 11.1 Electrical Safety\par
\par
**Overcurrent Protection:**\par
```\par
Primary: Fast-blow fuse, 7.5A, 250V\par
Secondary: Electronic trip, software-controlled, 6.5A threshold\par
Tertiary: MOSFET desaturation detection, 10A threshold\par
Response time: < 10 \'b5s\par
```\par
\par
**Overvoltage Protection:**\par
```\par
Input: Transorb, 150V clamping\par
Output: Crowbar circuit (SCR + 120V zener)\par
Capacitor bank: Bleeder resistor, 10k\f2\lang1032\'d9, 10W\par
Discharge time to < 50V: < 5 seconds after power off\par
```\par
\par
**Grounding:**\par
```\par
Single-point ground star configuration\par
Ground impedance: < 0.1\'d9 at 148.5 kHz\par
Chassis ground: Green wire, 12 AWG\par
Isolation: Opto-isolated control signals\par
```\par
\par
### 11.2 Thermal Safety\par
\par
**Temperature Monitoring:**\par
```\par
Sensors: 4 \f0\lang1033\'d7 thermistors (10k\f2\lang1032\'d9 @ 25\f0\lang1033\'b0C, NTC)\par
Locations: Coil, plate, heatsink, ambient\par
Thresholds:\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Warning at 50\'b0C\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Power reduction at 60\'b0C\par
\f7\u9500?\u9472?\f0  Emergency shutdown at 70\'b0C\par
\f7\u9492?\u9472?\f0  Hardware cutoff at 80\'b0C (thermal fuse)\par
```\par
\par
**Cooling Failure Detection:**\par
```\par
Flow sensor on liquid cooling: < 0.2 GPM triggers alarm\par
TEC current monitor: Open circuit detected\par
Fan tachometer: < 1000 RPM triggers alarm\par
All failures initiate controlled shutdown\par
```\par
\par
### 11.3 Radiation Safety (if applicable)\par
\par
**EMI Shielding:**\par
```\par
Enclosure: Mu-metal lined aluminum\par
Aperture: Conductive mesh or window with ITO coating\par
Shielding effectiveness: > 60 dB at 148.5 kHz\par
Test: Measure field at 1m distance, < 10 \'b5T\par
```\par
\par
**Warning Labels:**\par
```\par
- "HIGH VOLTAGE - 120V DC" on power supply\par
- "STRONG MAGNETIC FIELD" on enclosure\par
- "HOT SURFACE - 70\'b0C MAX" on heatsink\par
- "LASER RADIATION - CLASS 3B" if using atomic magnetometer\par
```\par
\par
### 11.4 Emergency Procedures\par
\par
**Power Failure:**\par
```\par
1. System automatically discharges capacitors (5 seconds)\par
2. UPS provides 5 minutes for controlled shutdown\par
3. Data logging continues on battery\par
4. All settings saved to non-volatile memory\par
```\par
\par
**Thermal Runaway:**\par
```\par
1. Hardware thermal fuse opens at 80\'b0C\par
2. Main contactor opens (disconnects AC power)\par
3. Audible alarm sounds\par
4. LED indicators flash red\par
5. System requires manual reset\par
```\par
\par
**Magnet Quench (cryogenic systems):**\par
```\par
1. Pressure relief valve opens at 5 PSI\par
2. Vent to outside (helium gas)\par
3. System isolates from power\par
4. Warning: Oxygen deficiency hazard\par
5. Area ventilation required\par
```\par
