### 15.6 Appendix D: Troubleshooting Guide\par
\par
| Symptom | Possible Cause | Solution |\par
|---------|---------------|----------|\par
| No resonance peak | Capacitor value wrong | Measure with LCR meter, replace |\par
| | Coil shorted | Check resistance, rewind if needed |\par
| | MOSFET not switching | Check gate drive waveform |\par
| Weak resonance | High ESR in capacitor | Replace with polypropylene |\par
| | Poor coil connections | Re-solder, check cold joints |\par
| | Magnetic array misaligned | Verify positions, realign |\par
| Null not found | Coil height wrong | Adjust Z-stage, rescan |\par
| | Current incorrect | Sweep current in finer steps |\par
| | Frequency off | Re-tune resonance |\par
| Thermal runaway | Insufficient cooling | Check fans, TEC power |\par
| | High ambient temperature | Reduce power or improve cooling |\par
| | Poor thermal interface | Reapply thermal compound |\par
| Frequency drift | Temperature variation | Improve thermal stabilization |\par
| | Power supply ripple | Add filtering capacitors |\par
| | Reference oscillator aging | Recalibrate, consider TCXO |\par
| EMI interference | Poor shielding | Check enclosure grounding |\par
| | Unshielded cables | Replace with shielded cables |\par
| | Ground loops | Implement star grounding |\par
| No Active-Silence | Multiple issues | Return to baseline, verify step by step |\par
